<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOTOR RACING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Japan's Takuya Kurosawa, driving a Lola T93 Mugen, defeated Andrew Scott of 
Britain by 15 seconds to win the fifth leg of the 10-race All Japan F-3000 
Championship at Sendai.Kurosawa, 31, is the first Japanese driver to win a 
F-3000 series race this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Ross Cheever of the United States, who started from the pole position, was 
fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 American Doug Polen and New Zealand's Aaron Slight teamed up to beat American 
Scott Russell and Briton Terry Rymer by 0.288 seconds in the 8-Hour Endurance 
motorcycle race at Suzuka, Japan. 
</P>
