<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: HESLINGTON, GONEAU PROMOTED; ADELMAN TO HEAD ANALYTIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Alan Adelman has been appointed president and chief executive of Irvine-based 
Analytic Investment Management Inc. Before joining Analytic Investment, 
Adelman, 40, was chief investment officer of First Interstate Bank of 
California, with overall responsibility for First Interstate's $10.4-billion 
investment management division. Analytic Investment Management, a pioneer in 
managing derivative securities, has about $1.2 billion in assets under 
management. Adelman succeeds Sheen Kassouf, who continues as chairman, and Alan 
Lewis will remain as chief investment officer and director of research. 
</P>
</TEXT>
