<HEADLINE>
<P>
5 KILLED IN S. AFRICA AS TV SHOW IS AIRED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gunmen shot dead at least five people in violence linked to a controversial TV 
drama implicating Zulu nationalists in a campaign of violence against rivals, 
police and human rights officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The killings coincided with the television broadcast Saturday night of "The 
Line," which depicted the effects of political violence on black train 
commuters and blames Zulu nationalists for attacking trains. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the killings occurred in three incidents in the black township of 
Ezikhaweni, 90 miles north of Durban. 
</P>
