<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN SHOT IN SPINE IN GANG INCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 21-year-old man was shot in the spine early Sunday morning in a gang-related 
incident at the corner of Sepulveda Boulevard and Roscoe Street, Los Angeles 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Nelson Ramirez of North Hollywood was shot in the back at 1:30 a.m. with a 9 
millimeter handgun, injuring his spinal chord. He was treated at Harbor-UCLA 
Medical Center in Torrance, where he was reported in stable condition, 
according to police. 
</P>
<P>
 Police reported no suspects in the shooting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
