<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN DIES IN ACCIDENT ON FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Acton woman died Sunday when her husband apparently lost control of their 
car and it rolled down a steep embankment off the Antelope Valley Freeway, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred about 11:15 a.m. on the north side of the freeway, said 
Officer Frank Lewis of the California Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim's husband and her two children were airlifted to Antelope Valley 
Hospital Medical Center in Lancaster, Lewis said. Their identities were not 
released. 
</P>
<P>
 A nursing supervisor at the hospital said she expected the children's father 
to be treated and released from the hospital Sunday, but said she could not 
provide information on the children's condition. 
</P>
<P>
 The crash is under investigation, Lewis said. 
</P>
