<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND PREVIEW / THE BUSINESS WEEK AHEAD: ORANGE COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Surfing to Ring Cash Registers: The U.S. Open of Surfing, the Assn. of Surfing 
Professionals' first world-class event on the U.S. mainland since 1991, opens 
Tuesday in Huntington Beach, and local merchants can hardly wait. The city 
expects a wave of business from surf fans and corporate affairs hosted by the 
event's sponsors, including Sebastian International Inc., a Woodland 
Hills-based hair products company that is bringing 2,000 distributors to 
town.Attendance at the weekend finals could soar to 100,000 fans daily. The 
cash-strapped city will get a boost as beach-goers pay to park in city-owned 
lots and eat at beachfront concession stands. Diane Baker, president of the 
Huntington Beach Conference and Visitors Bureau, said televised coverage of the 
contest by cable network Prime Ticket "is publicity that you can't buy." 
</P>
</TEXT>
