<P>
 Ford Recalls School Buses, Pickup Trucks: The auto maker recalled about 6,000 
of its 1987-94 school buses in 14 Upper Midwest and Northeastern states and 
eastern Canadian provinces to replace electrical components in the chassis. 
About 900 of the 1994 F-series pickup trucks were recalled to replace faulty 
7.3-liter direct injection turbo diesel engines and manual transmissions. 
