<P>
 Los Angeles-based Foothill Group Inc. increased its quarterly dividend to 6 
cents from 5 cents on its Class A common stock, payable on Oct. 20 to 
shareholders of record on Sept. 20. . . . Chrysler Corp. said the suggested 
retail prices of its 1995 cars and trucks will be an average of 2% higher than 
prices of comparably equipped 1994 models. . . . Nissan Motor Corp. said prices 
for 1995 Nissan cars and trucks will be an average of 3.8% higher than prices 
on comparably equipped 1994 models. The average increase is $711 per vehicle. . 
. . Campbell Soup Co. said it will buy back as many as 7.5 million shares, or 
about 3% of its 251 million common shares outstanding.Shares will be bought 
from time to time on the open market. . . . Richmond, Va.-based Signet Banking 
Corp. plans to cut 1,000, or 17%, of its jobs by 1995 in an effort to slash a 
quarter of its expenses. 
