<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: ENERGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Unocal to Offer Food and a Fill-Up: Drivers will be able to order lunch and 
fill their tank at the same time beginning today at a Unocal Corp. station just 
off I-5 at Lebec. The arrangement between Unocal and Nathan's Famous Inc. -- 
owner of a family restaurant chain that lays claim to the original Coney Island 
Hot Dog -- includes menus attached to the gasoline pumps and intercoms that 
allow drivers to order fast food while they refuel, to be ready to eat when 
they pick it up.The feature is part of several improvements Unocal plans to 
make at about 200 of its stations. Another change: pumps that fill gas tanks 
40% faster than many of those now in stations. 
</P>
