<P>
 Mobil Reports Loss: The oil company said it will take a $680-million non-cash 
charge against second-quarter earnings reported earlier this week, to reflect a 
change in accounting for inventories. The restatement will wipe out the 
Fairfax, Va.-based company's second-quarter profit of $535 million, or $1.31 a 
share, leaving it with a loss of $145 million, or 40 cents a share. 
