</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Company Licensed to Manufacture Aircraft Tires: Guilin Lanyu Aviation Tires 
Development Co. of Guilin received the first such license China has granted.It 
will make the tires for nine models of large passenger planes, including ones 
built by Boeing Co. and McDonnell Douglas Corp., the official News Agency 
Xinhua reported, citing official sources. China joins the small number of 
countries -- the United States, Britain and Japan among them -- that 
manufacture aircraft tires. Lanyu Aviation took five years to develop the tires 
as part of China's Torch Program, which provides funds for high-technology 
research. Guilin is in southwestern China. 
</P>
