<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SOUTH COUNTY; A CLASS FOR DRIVERS GOING OVER 50 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Senior citizens who want to sharpen their motoring skills and qualify for 
insurance discounts can sign up for driving classes throughout the area this 
month. 
</P>
<P>
 The courses show motorists how to adjust their driving skills as they 
age.Those completing the two-day course also qualify for car insurance 
discounts. 
</P>
<P>
 The program, called "55 Alive," is sponsored by the American Assn. of Retired 
Persons, and participants must be at least age 50. 
</P>
<P>
 The cost is $8, and preregistration is required. 
</P>
<P>
 Upon finishing the class, students are given a certificate of completion that 
automobile insurance companies honor for good-driving discounts. 
</P>
<P>
 Those interested in signing up must contact the facility where the class is 
being held. Classes in South County during August include: 
</P>
<P>
 * Wednesday and Thursday from 1 to 5 p.m. at Iglesia Community Center, 24671 
Via Iglesia, Laguna Hills. (714) 380-0155. 
</P>
<P>
 * Aug. 8 and 9 from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. at San Juan Capistrano Regional Library, 
31495 El Camino Real, in San Juan Capistrano. (714) 493-5911. 
</P>
<P>
 * Aug. 8 from 9 from 9:30 a.m. to 2 p.m. at San Clemente Senior Citizen 
Center, 242 Del Mar, in San Clemente. (714) 498-3322. 
</P>
<P>
 * Aug. 18 and 19 from 1 to 5 p.m. at Glendale Federal Bank, 24221 Calle de la 
Louisa, Laguna Hills. (714) 768-7771. 
</P>
<P>
 * Aug. 20 and 27 from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. at Laguna Beach Senior Center in Lang 
Park at Wesley and Coast Highway. (714) 497-2441. 
</P>
<P>
 * Aug. 24 and 31 from 9:30 a.m. to 2 p.m. at Capistrano Bay Park and 
Recreation District offices, 34052 Del Obispo Road. (714) 496-4251. FRANK 
MESSINA 
</P>
