TOURIST KILLED WALKING ACROSS FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A tourist from Coventry, England, who wandered onto the Costa Mesa Freeway 
early Sunday was struck by a car and killed, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Paul Clive Straiton, 38, was pronounced dead at Hoag Memorial Hospital 
Presbyterian about 1 a.m., according to a statement issued by Sgt. D. Walker. 
The driver, an 18-year-old Fountain Valley man, was not cited, Walker said. 
</P>
