<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOUNTAIN VALLEY SPIRIT WINS NATIONAL GIRLS' SOCCER TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Fountain Valley Spirit won the U.S. Youth Soccer under-18 girls' 
championship Sunday, defeating Connecticut Omni, 2-1, Sunday in Blaine, Minn. 
</P>
<P>
 Spirit defender Jillian Lipscomb scored on a 19-yard shot into the right 
corner 30 seconds after Omni had tied the score, 1-1, in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley, which finished 63-2, took a 1-0 lead when midfielder Monica 
Gerado scored on a volley from 12 yards out in the 61st minute. 
</P>
<P>
 Connecticut, which won the under-17 title last year, was attempting to become 
the first team to win consecutive titles. 
</P>
