<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATIONAL ROUNDUP; TABASCO CAT IS SECOND IN SARATOGA'S JIM DANDY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Unaccounted For held off Preakness and Belmont winner Tabasco Cat to win the 
Grade II Jim Dandy Stakes by a length at Saratoga Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Unaccounted For, a well-beaten second in the mud in his previous start as the 
odds-on favorite, flourished on the firmer footing this time, covering 1 1/8 
miles on the fast track in 1:49 2/5. 
</P>
<P>
 Unaccounted For, who paid $6.80, was also the recipient of a 14-pound weight 
break from Tabasco Cat. Both Unaccounted For and Tabasco Cat are expected to 
run against Holy Bull in the Travers Stakes on Aug. 20. 
</P>
<P>
 Holy Bull led the 1 1/8-mile Haskell Invitational Handicap at Monmouth Park 
wire to wire, winning by 1 3/4 lengths. 
</P>
<P>
 He was timed in 1:48 1/5 and paid $2.40. Meadow Flight was second, Concern 
third. 
</P>
