<P>
NFL EXHIBITIONS; SWITZER WINS COWBOY DEBUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Barry Switzer's NFL exhibition debut was successful Sunday night, thanks to a 
player he recruited out of Henryetta (Okla.)High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Troy Aikman threw a touchdown pass and the defending Super Bowl champion 
Dallas Cowboys defeated the Minnesota Vikings, 17-9, at Irving, Tex. 
</P>
<P>
 Aikman who played for Switzer at Oklahoma in 1985 before transferring to UCLA 
one year later. 
</P>
<P>
 Switzer was hired by owner Jerry Jones on March 30 to replace Jimmy Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
 Kansas City 24, Houston 17 -- Alex Van Pelt hit Lee Harris with a 25-yard 
touchdown pass with 18 seconds left, giving the Chiefs a victory in the first 
game on the new grass field at Arrowhead Stadium in Kansas City. 
</P>
