<HEADLINE>
<P>
THIEF MAY HAVE DIANA'S RECORDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Princess Diana returned Sunday night from vacation in Spain to face the 
possibility that her confidential medical records had been stolen and might 
become public. 
</P>
<P>
 Police confirmed that files were stolen July 22 from the office of her 
therapist in London. 
</P>
<P>
 The files are thought to contain intimate revelations of her physical and 
mental health during the breakdown of her marriage to Prince Charles. 
</P>
<P>
 They were contained in a small computer used by Roderick Lane, a clinical 
nutritionist who treated Diana during a reported struggle with bulimia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA080194-0157 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 066091 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
August 1, 1994, Monday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
