<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; 2 SEEK REELECTION TO SCHOOL BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Oxnard School District board members have announced that they will run for 
reelection in November. 
</P>
<P>
 James J. Suter, 68, has filed his candidacy papers with the county election's 
office, and Mary Barreto, 59, said she plans to do so this week.Both candidates 
are seeking a second term on the board. 
</P>
<P>
 Jack T. Fowler, 60, said he planned to step down in December after 20 years on 
the board of trustees. Fowler said he may begin writing a newsletter that 
covers school issues in Ventura County. 
</P>
<P>
 Barreto, who began campaigning in May, is a family therapist and a professor 
at Cal State Northridge. Barreto said she wants to continue playing a role in 
the education of Oxnard children. 
</P>
<P>
 "My experience in the first four years will help me to become a more effective 
board member," Barreto said. 
</P>
<P>
 Suter, who retired as a teacher in 1987 after working 35 years for the Oxnard 
School District, said he is seeking another four-year term on the board because 
his work with children is not complete. 
</P>
<P>
 "I still have a lot do," Suter said. "And I want to get parents more involved 
in the education of their children." CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA080194-0174 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 066108 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
