<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; RECYCLING PROGRAM WINNERS HONORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nine Camarillo companies or organizations were honored last week by the City 
Council for their recycling efforts. 
</P>
<P>
 Gold award winners in the city's 1994 WasteWatch program included: 
</P>
<P>
 Siemens Solar Industries, for best resource conservation program; Bill's Bike 
Shop for buying and best use of recycled products; St. John's Pleasant Valley 
Hospital for best institutional recycling program; Jiffy Lube for best motor 
oil recycling; Kids, Moms & More, a specialty store, for best reuse of 
materials. 
</P>
<P>
 Anderson, Arstein, Roland and Sprague, a Camarillo dental group practice, and 
Sturman Industries, Inc. a valve manufacturer, received silver awards. Two 
Pleasant Valley School District facilities -- Las Posas Elementary and Monte 
Vista Intermediate -- also won special awards. 
</P>
<P>
 "With the dedication of businesses and organizations like our 1994 WasteWatch 
winners," said Mayor Ken Gose, "our city is well on its way to meeting our goal 
of reducing wastes by 25% in 1995 and 50% by the year 2000." J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
