<HEADLINE>
<P>
GUNMAN RESPONSIBLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Recently, a senseless act of violence in Thousand Oaks by a 17-year-old young 
man led to the death of an innocent girl whose only mistake was to be an 
acquaintance. Any person of responsible age should have the right to keep and 
bear arms as they see fit, and not answer to anyone on that account alone. 
</P>
<P>
 Any person who pulls out a weapon and murders an innocent party in the name of 
fun and games or stupidity is fully responsible for his or her actions. 
</P>
<P>
 According to a newspaper account, the admitted act of this young adult 
occurred after the weapon had been in his possession for a week, and he had 
pointed the loaded gun at several other people before it discharged -- taking 
the life of an innocent girl. The article went on to say his lawyer would use 
the defense that gun laws need to be strengthened to prevent this kind of 
accident. 
</P>
<P>
 Any judge who would allow an act like this to be viewed as one of reckless 
youth and attorneys who would use a defense of not enough laws as an excuse for 
a stupid, irresponsible act of violence are themselves largely responsible for 
the degradation of morality, rampant crime and lack of common decency our 
nation is experiencing. 
</P>
<P>
 Capital crimes deserve capital punishment. Incidents of homicide by any person 
of responsible age by knowingly playing with a loaded gun must never be viewed 
as just a youthful mistake. 
</P>
<P>
 JIM NICHOLS, Thousand Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
